(A) What Problem ControlValueAccessor Solves

Without ControlValueAccessor:

Angular forms cannot communicate with custom components.

Example problem:

formControlName will not work with custom components.

ControlValueAccessor solves this by connecting the custom component to the Angular forms system.

(B)Core Methods of ControlValueAccessor

ControlValueAccessor has four important methods.

1. writeValue()

Called by Angular when the form model updates.

Used to set the value inside the component.

Example idea:

Form sets value → component UI updates.

2. registerOnChange()

Angular provides a function to track value changes.

Component must call this function whenever the user changes value.

Example idea:

User clicks star rating → update form value.

3. registerOnTouched()

Angular provides a function to track touch events.

Component must call it when the user interacts with the control.

Example idea:

User clicks input → control becomes touched.

4. setDisabledState() (optional)

Called when the form control becomes disabled or enabled.

Used to disable UI elements inside the component.

Example idea:

disable button or input field.


(C) ControlValueAccessor Workflow

Flow of communication:

Form Model → Component UI

writeValue()

Component UI → Form Model

registerOnChange()

Touch Interaction

registerOnTouched()

Disabled State

setDisabledState()

